state.unicode: Your clan has grown too powerful - the Shogunate is forging an alliance against you and your allies. You are the enemy of the state!
The Shogun sees your clan as a potentional threat.
There is little knowledge of your clan.
Most of the Japanese people heard about your clan.

uientry.unicode: Clan fame is gained by fighting battles and conquering provinces and is also influenced by other factors, such as your daimyo's honour.||As your clan's fame increases, others will start to notice you and the shogunate itself may come to view your clan as a threat to its rule.
